ouglass\"}, {\"begin\": 910, \"end\": 922, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 0.9984831641847408, \"rank\": 0.0011146497426195393, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 986, \"end\": 994, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999731103497563, \"rank\": 0.0002422618648353717, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"KATE DOUGLASS STRIKES GOLD IN THE 200M BREASTSTROKE.\", \"from\": 1055, \"to\": 1107, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00f0\\u009f\\u00a5\\u0087\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00ba\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00b8#ParisOlympics| \\u00f0\\u009f\\u0093\\u00ba NBC and Peacockpic.twitter.com/ZtNpUGcnjg  Her second gold came on the final day of competition, after Douglass had already finished all of her swims for the week.\", \"from\": 1108, \"to\": 1304, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1141, \"end\": 1144, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9999997947297954, \"rank\": 1.9025848876544587e-07, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 1244, \"end\": 1252, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frederick_Douglass\", \"score\": 0.8115369128272346, \"rank\": 0.2322298396954049, \"text\": \"Douglass\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frederick_Douglass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frederick_Douglass\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since she swam in the prelims on Team USA's 4x100 medley relay team, Douglass and fellow Wahoo Emma Weber, who also swam in the prelims, both earned gold medals whenGretchen Walsh and company topped the field in the final.Earlier in the week, Douglass picked up a silver medal in the 200 individual medley, the same event in which she won a bronze medal in Tokyo, and also swam as part of the 4x100 free relay team that won silver on the first night of swimming competition in Paris.\", \"from\": 1305, \"to\": 1788, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1338, \"end\": 1346, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.9136440514912074, \"rank\": 0.09451811535912369, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1374, \"end\": 1382, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frederick_Douglass\", \"score\": 0.8115369128272346, \"rank\": 0.2322298396954049, \"text\": \"Douglass\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frederick_Douglass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frederick_Douglass\"}, {\"begin\": 1400, \"end\": 1404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tenille_Dashwood\", \"score\": 0.9998723578029746, \"rank\": 9.238376572593803e-05, \"text\": \"Emma\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tenille_Dashwood\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tenille_Dashwood\"}, {\"begin\": 1405, \"end\": 1410, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Weber_carburetor\", \"score\": 0.6781295050777282, \"rank\": 0.20737056502313117, \"text\": \"Weber\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Weber_carburetor\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Weber_carburetor\"}, {\"begin\": 1548, \"end\": 1556, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frederick_Douglass\", \"score\": 0.8115369128272346, \"rank\": 0.2322298396954049, \"text\": \"Douglass\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frederick_Douglass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frederick_Douglass\"}, {\"begin\": 1662, \"end\": 1667, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.5742123263027804, \"rank\": 0.7415160440811548, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1782, \"end\": 1787, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999629944802, \"rank\": 3.7005636484315635e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gretchen Walsh, who was making her Olympic debut, also swam as part of that opening-night 4x100 free relay team and so earned her first Olympic medal.\", \"from\": 1790, \"to\": 1940, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1790, \"end\": 1804, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gretchen Walsh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After setting an Olympic record in the semifinals of the 100 butterfly, Walsh came up just short to American teammate Torri Huske in the final to capture silver, her first individual Olympic medal.Walsh earned her first gold medals on the final two days of the competition, swimming the butterfly leg ofTeam USA's mixed 4x100 medley relay that broke a world recordand needed every bit of it to hold off China for gold.\", \"from\": 1941, \"to\": 2359, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2041, \"end\": 2049, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999731103497563, \"rank\": 0.0002422618648353717, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2059, \"end\": 2070, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torri_Huske\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Torri Huske\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torri_Huske\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torri_Huske\"}, {\"begin\": 2249, \"end\": 2252, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9950199278815698, \"rank\": 0.003321340550403497, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2344, \"end\": 2349, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8668103170809328, \"rank\": 0.13752692160711963, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The next night, Walsh again swam the butterfly leg as part of the women's 4x100 medley relay, matching the fastest butterfly relay split ever recorded (55.03 seconds) to help Regan Smith, Lilly King, and Torri Huske demolish the previous world record in the event by nearly a full second and run away with another gold medal.\", \"from\": 2360, \"to\": 2685, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2535, \"end\": 2546, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.027126125542549e-26, \"text\": \"Regan Smith\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\"}, {\"begin\": 2548, \"end\": 2553, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eli_Lilly_and_Company\", \"score\": 0.9997896445177438, \"rank\": 0.00012342103354989338, \"text\": \"Lilly\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eli_Lilly_and_Company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eli_Lilly_and_Company\"}, {\"begin\": 2554, \"end\": 2558, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Art_of_Fighting\", \"score\": 0.8519567321124144, \"rank\": 0.1643767031654222, \"text\": \"King\", \"types\": [\"Q7889\", \"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Art_of_Fighting\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Art_of_Fighting\"}, {\"begin\": 2564, \"end\": 2575, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torri_Huske\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Torri Huske\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torri_Huske\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torri_Huske\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00f0\\u009f\\u00a5\\u0087\\u00f0\\u009d\\u0090\\u0086\\u00f0\\u009d\\u0090\\u008e\\u00f0\\u009d\\u0090\\u008b\\u00f0\\u009d\\u0090\\u0083 \\u00f0\\u009d\\u0090\\u008c\\u00f0\\u009d\\u0090\\u0084\\u00f0\\u009d\\u0090\\u0083\\u00f0\\u009d\\u0090\\u0080\\u00f0\\u009d\\u0090\\u008b\\u00f0\\u009d\\u0090\\u0088\\u00f0\\u009d\\u0090\\u0092\\u00f0\\u009d\\u0090\\u0093\\u00f0\\u009d\\u0090\\u0092\\u00f0\\u009f\\u00a5\\u0087Emma Weber and Kate Douglass also win gold with the 4x100 Medley Relay.\", \"from\": 2687, \"to\": 2819, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2753, \"end\": 2758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Weber_carburetor\", \"score\": 0.6781295050777282, \"rank\": 0.20737056502313117, \"text\": \"Weber\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Weber_carburetor\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Weber_carburetor\"}, {\"begin\": 2763, \"end\": 2776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kate Douglass\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\"}, {\"begin\": 2800, \"end\": 2818, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_1988_Summer_Olympics_\\u2013_Men's_4_\\u00d7_100_metre_medley_relay\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"4x100 Medley Relay\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_1988_Summer_Olympics_\\u2013_Men's_4_\\u00d7_100_metre_medley_relay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_1988_Summer_Olympics_\\u2013_Men's_4_\\u00d7_100_metre_medley_relay\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Emma swam the breaststroke leg and Kate the freestyle anchor leg in yesterday's prelim#OlympiansMadeHere|#Paris2024|#GoHoospic.twitter.com/eskqNdpz6s  Paige Madden teamed up with Katie Ledecky and helped the legendary swimmer win her record-breaking 13th medal, capturing silver in the 4x200 free relay.\", \"from\": 2820, \"to\": 3123, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2820, \"end\": 2824, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tenille_Dashwood\", \"score\": 0.9998723578029746, \"rank\": 9.238376572593803e-05, \"text\": \"Emma\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tenille_Dashwood\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tenille_Dashwood\"}, {\"begin\": 2855, \"end\": 2859, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Ramsay\", \"score\": 0.9382592345103695, \"rank\": 0.05242114094819582, \"text\": \"Kate\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Ramsay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Ramsay\"}, {\"begin\": 2971, \"end\": 2983, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paige_Madden\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paige Madden\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paige_Madden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paige_Madden\"}, {\"begin\": 2999, \"end\": 3012, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then, Madden shared the podium with Ledecky in the 800 free, lowering her personal best by more than five seconds to earn bronze, her first-ever individual Olympic medal.\", \"from\": 3124, \"to\": 3294, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3130, \"end\": 3136, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madden_NFL\", \"score\": 0.9999999704205043, \"rank\": 2.957914726117925e-08, \"text\": \"Madden\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madden_NFL\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madden_NFL\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Six of Virginia's medals were earned in the final two days of swimming events this past weekend, a stretch during which Team USA surged from behind to finish atop the gold medal table in the Olympic swimming competition.\", \"from\": 3296, \"to\": 3516, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3303, \"end\": 3311, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Virginia_Cavaliers_men's_basketball\", \"score\": 0.9855518598532035, \"rank\": 0.008956376717488815, \"text\": \"Virginia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Virginia_Cavaliers_men's_basketball\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Virginia_Cavaliers_men's_basketball\"}, {\"begin\": 3416, \"end\": 3424, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.9136440514912074, \"rank\": 0.09451811535912369, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The United States' top swimming rival, Australia, had held the lead for most of the meet, but the Americans stormed ahead on the last day and finished up 8-7 in gold medals and 28-18 in total medals.\", \"from\": 3517, \"to\": 3716, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3521, \"end\": 3534, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999812981380135, \"rank\": 1.821141356798804e-05, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The efforts of these UVA swimmers as well as Virginia head coach Todd DeSorbo, who served as head coach of the United States Women's Olympic Swimming Team, were a big part of Team USA's success in the pool at these Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 3718, \"to\": 3947, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3739, \"end\": 3742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Virginia_Cavaliers_men's_basketball\", \"score\": 0.8685551703688126, \"rank\": 0.151292686526443, \"text\": \"UVA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Virginia_Cavaliers_men's_basketball\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Virginia_Cavaliers_men's_basketball\"}, {\"begin\": 3763, \"end\": 3771, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Virginia_Cavaliers_men's_basketball\", \"score\": 0.9855518598532035, \"rank\": 0.008956376717488815, \"text\": \"Virginia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Virginia_Cavaliers_men's_basketball\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Virginia_Cavaliers_men's_basketball\"}, {\"begin\": 3